Incident.Summary: FATAL ACRS. VEHICLE VS PED. PED AT FAULT.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
Maryland State Police
Berlin Barrack “V” (9096)
TFC R. Phillips #7211
September 11th, 2023


Maryland State Police Patrol Vehicle – V-16 is a marked Ford Explorer that is equipped with an MVR system. This incident was also audibly and visually recorded on Axon Body Camera. All videos associated with the incident labeled (23MSP031891).

Deceased Person -
  • Name: Muhammed Enes Ekinci
  • DOB: 09/16/2002
  • Social: 800-92-5016
  • J1 (I-94) Record number: 38997083A3
  • Visa Passport #: S21147830

Narrative:

   On September 11, 2023 at 0601 hours, troopers from the Berlin Barrack, were dispatched to the westbound US Route 50 at Highway 589 for a vehicle vs pedestrian accident.

   Upon arrival, a white male was located in the grassy median with severe injuries. He was unresponsive. EMS arrived on scene prior to our arrival. Worcester County Deputies and EMS performed CPR on the male. He was then transported to Atlantic General Hospital via Berlin EMS (23-005870).

  I then contacted the female operator of the striking vehicle. She was identified through her Maryland Driver’s license as Katie Tucker (DOB: 10/12/1977). She advised she was going 55 mph in lane 1 on westbound US RT 50. After passing the light at the intersection of US RT 50 and Brader Lane, she advised a person on a scooter crossed in front of her suddenly. The scooter operator had pulled out of the grassy median. She did not have enough time to swerve out of the way. She struck the scooter operator, running him over. She advised she felt “two bumps” and then pulled to the left shoulder.
 
   I observed the 2011 Ford sedan to have its front bumper ripped off and the undercarriage of the vehicle to be damaged. The vehicle was deemed drivable and allowed to leave the scene at the conclusion of the investigation with approval from the Crash Team.

  After speaking to Tucker, I spoke to two witnesses Kelly Rae Hendrix and Edwin Jonathan Zelaya. Zelaya was parked at the McDonalds at the time of the accident. He advised he saw a person in dark clothing on the scooter attempting to cross US RT 50. He heard the collision and drove to the scene. While at the scene, he observed the debris and the vehicle that struck the person. Hendrix was 3-4 car lengths behind the striking vehicle. She advised she believed both her and 2011 ford to be going between 55 mph and 60 mph. She advised it was dark and foggy. She advised she could not see any pedestrians. She advised she heard the collision and saw the ford swerve to the left after striking something in the road. She advised she pulled to the right shoulder where she saw a shoe and a scooter in lane 1.

  An accident reconstructionist was requested, TFC Repa responded to the scene. Further interviews were conducted on scene, including a written statement by Katie Tucker.

   McDonalds, Verizon, Walmart, Raceway Citgo Inc, and Crabs To Go were checked for cameras. None of the businesses had camera footage of the accident.

   The deceased was identified by several friends who were in the area. His identity was confirmed by his employer Ocean Pines Food Lion. His family was notified by Turkish authorities. The Turkish embassy along with Alliance Abroad Group are claiming the body and have contacted the medical examiner's office. Chuck Ward (ME) responded to the scene. An MSP 89B has been attached to this report along with the written statement. $12.30 and two cellular phones belonging to the deceased were located and processed. All items were placed in the Barrack "V" property room. 

All events occurred in Worcester County, Maryland.

Narrartive:

   Originally the camera at Raceway Citgo was not recording. After contacting their security service, they were able to get video. The video shows the scooter cut through the Citgo parking lot then go eastbound in westbound US RT 50 the wrong way. The scooter cuts across lane 2 into lane 1 and continues the wrong way. The scooter then is struck by the vehicle. 

This case has been forwarded to the Crash team. All events occurred in Worcester County, MD.

Detailed Crash Investigation Report
(For review by the MSP Crash Team)

Agency: Maryland State Police
Case Number- 23-MSP-031891


Section I. - Introduction: 
On September 11, 2023, at approximately 0601 hours, Troopers from the Maryland State Police Berlin Barrack were dispatched to the area of Ocean Gateway at Racetrack Road, Berlin, Worcester County, Maryland for a vehicle versus pedestrian strike with personal injuries. Upon the arrival of Berlin Barrack State Troopers, they learned that the strike involved the listed vehicle and persons.

Pedestrian: Muhammed Enes Ekinci (DOB 09/26/2002 O/M) (Deceased)

Electric Scooter: Evercross

Vehicle 2: 2011 Ford Fusion, MD 4DZ1640 VIN: 3FAHP0HGXBR275481

Driver/Registered owner: Katie Marie Tucker (DOB 10/12/1977 W/F)

Upon MSP Berlin Troopers arriving onscene, they observed Emergency Medical Services (EMS) performing CPR on the pedestrian in the grassy center median. EMS advised the Troopers that they were ground transporting Ekinci to Atlantic General Hospital with run #23-005870.

MSP Berlin Barrack contacted the MSP Easton Barrack to request reconstruction/Advanced collision investigator to conduct a post-crash investigation. I, TFC. Repa #7124 of the Maryland State Police Easton Barrack trained as an Advanced Collision Investigator, responded to the call at 0621 hours.

While enroute, I was informed the pedestrian in the collision was declared deceased at 0625 hours by Hospital personnel.

Upon my arrival, I made contact with TFC. Phillips from MSP Berlin Barrack on scene that stated the Ford sedan was traveling westbound on Ocean Gateway at the intersection of Brader Lane in lane 1 when an electric scooter came across the intersection at Brader Lane. The electric scooter went infront of the Ford sedans lane of travel and was struck in the front bumper area by the Ford sedan. The roadway was dry, and the weather was foggy. I was also advised that the electric scooter was moved by other motorist to the center median to avoid another collision.

I made contact with the operator of the Ford Fusion (Katie Tucker). Tucker advised she did not see the electric scooter and only realized she struck the pedestrian/scooter when she felt two bumps from running over the scooter. Tucker advised the weather was foggy at the time of the collision. Tucker advised the traffic signal at the intersection was displaying a solid green light which gave her the right of way. Lastly, the operator of the Ford sedan advised me after impact she safely pulled onto the left shoulder at a controlled stop to avoid additional collisions due to the fog.

I then proceeded to review the scene and upon completion began taking digital photographs of marked roadway evidence and the vehicles involved to document the scene. The Ford sedan had front end damage with the lower front bumper falling off due to impact with the scooter. The Ford sedan did not display any tire marks due to coming to a controlled stop. The scooter was also moved from final rest for safety reasons by citizens. A mark in the pavement displayed the initial impact with the Ford sedan and the scooter.

Section II. - Scene Description: (The following descriptions are based on the area where the collision occurred.)

Primary Roadway:  Ocean Gateway(US 50)
 
Ocean Gateway is a United States divided highway that travels in an east and west direction. The roadway has two lanes of travel in each direction. The below photograph is facing the westbound direction approaching the Racetrack Road cross street and the point of view Tucker had prior to the collision. The westbound side of Ocean Gateway consists of the roadway traveling straight through a three-way junction. Each way of travel on Ocean Gateway had an operational traffic signal for traffic merging onto Ocean Gateway. The speed limit on Ocean Gateway at the junction is 55 miles per hour.


The above image captured from google maps, which accurately depicts Ocean Gateway prior to Brader Lane intersection as described above.


Image 2220 shows the first circle as the point of impact between the electric scooter and Ford sedan on Ocean Gateway at Racetrack Road.

The roadway on Ocean Gateway was constructed with paved asphalt material and appeared to be in good condition with no defects. The roadway markings were clear, and the roadway surface was dry at the time of crash. The traffic signal at the intersection was operational at the time of impact and working properly.


The above image captured from the MDOT SHA Speed limit map, which accurately depicts the posted speed limit on Ocean Gateway at Brader Lane.

Environmental Conditions:
The environmental conditions at the time of crash were of the following.
  • Surface Air Temperature- Approximately 71 degrees Fahrenheit
  • Cloud Cover- mostly cloudy
  • Wind conditions- 5 mph
  • Precipitation- 0 inches
  • Sunrise/Sunset- 0645/1924 hours
Obtained information from www.Weatherunderground.com


The collision occurred during early morning hours. Lighting consisted of vehicle headlights and streetlamps.
Section III. - Scene Evidence:
  • I began documenting the scene from the east side of where the collision occurred. As I walked west towards the collision, I did not locate pre-impact tire markings from either the Ford sedan and scooter. I did not locate any post impact tire marks. The Ford sedan and scooter were both moved after coming to final rest. I did locate main impact in the center of lane 1 on the roadway and documented the impact. I also located where the pedestrian had landed after impact and documented the location.

Section V. - Person(s) Involved:

Person #1: Pedestrian

Section VI. - Follow-up Investigation:

Citgo gas station was contacted by Berlin Troopers in regard to a video footage. Video footage from the Citgo was sent to TFC Phillips and myself from Shore Security Systems for review. The footage displays the pedestrian coming across the Citgo gas station parking lot. After the parking lot it shows the pedestrian traveling across lane 2 and 1 traveling eastbound in the westbound lanes. While traveling in lane 1, the scooter/pedestrian was shown being struck by the Ford sedan as a head on collision. 
 
Section VII. - Analysis of Electronic Control Modules:
No electronic control modules were located in the area of the collision.
 
Section VIII. - Speed Analysis:
No Speed Analysis was completed during the investigation.

 
Section IX. - Crash Dynamics:
The Crash Dynamics were determined by on scene evidence.


The Ford sedan, operated by Katie Tucker, was traveling eastbound at the intersection on Ocean Gateway at Brader Lane in lane 1. The pedestrian, Muhammed Enes Ekinci, on an electric scooter was traveling eastbound prior to the intersection on Ocean Gateway at Brader Lane in the westbound lanes in lane 1. View for both involved was limited due to the density of fog. The Ford sedan passed the intersection approximately 25 feet when it struck the pedestrian's scooter in a head on collision. The Ford sedan struck the pedestrian in the front bumper more on the driver's side. The scooter went under the Ford sedan taking off the front bumper. After impact, the pedestrian went airborne and landed in the grassy center median. The pedestrian traveled approximately 30 feet from impact to the final landing area. After impact the Ford sedan came to a controlled stop after impact approximately 100 feet on the left shoulder.
